path.id: Letâ€™s assess the problem in the world of agriculture from a climate change point of view. How is agriculture related to the phenomenon of climate change? In Figure 4, you can see a visualization in which you learn how much greenhouse gas some of the common farm animals we consume emit. It is important for us to understand the environmental impact that these animals have on our planet, as we create the demand for them to be bred. From Figure 4, we are able to see that beef,which comes from cattle, is one of the most significant polluters of a greenhouse gas called methane. This gas is not as abundant as carbon dioxide, but it is much worse in terms of the effect that it has on the environment. Additionally, poultry, containing mostly chicken, ducks, turkey and geese, are found to be the smallest polluters of methane. These animals are the main ingredient in many of the fast foods that we eat daily. Therefore, increasing the demand for these foods, and hence the meat, contribute to the increase in the amount of greenhouse gas emission. So, the little actions you take everyday, such as buying fried chicken, are not only bad for your health, but the well-being of the planet as well! We hope that you consider the food you decide to eat, because every small thing makes a difference.
